    "faq_K3AkYN": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "tab_content_K3gYWL": {
          "type": "tab_content",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need an appointment to visit the showroom?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>You are always welcome to browse our showroom without an appointment. However, if you would like to discuss a bespoke design, view engagement rings, or speak to our repair specialists, we highly recommend booking a consultation to ensure a dedicated jeweller is available to assist you.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "tab_content_D79G6Y": {
          "type": "tab_content",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does a bespoke jewellery commission take?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>A bespoke piece typically takes between 4 to 6 weeks to craft from the moment the final design is approved. This timeline can vary slightly depending on the complexity of the piece and the sourcing of specific gemstones.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "tab_content_N9dmTB": {
          "type": "tab_content",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you buy old or scrap gold?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>Unfortunately we don't buy gold at Griffin & Co, however we would recommend visiting our sister business, <a href=\"https://www.ebonyjewellery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.ebonyjewellery.com/\">Ebony Jewellers </a>who offer competitive rates for your scrap gold, which can be exchanged for cash or used as credit towards a new purchase, repair, or a remodelling project.</p>",
